3.00	Grant_v._Torstar_Corp.	Grant v. Torstar Corp.	Grant v. Torstar Corp., _ S.C.R. _, 2009 SCC 61, is a 2009 Supreme Court of Canada decision on the defences to the tort of defamation. In it, the Supreme Court ruled that the law of defamation should give way to the rights of a party to speak on matters of public interest, provided party exercises a certain level of responsibility in verifying the potentially defamatory facts. That is, the Court recognized a defence of responsible communication on matters of public interest.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/28/Supreme_Court_of_Canada_2.jpg/200px-Supreme_Court_of_Canada_2.jpg
